Package: customizeGeneSets
Title: Build Defensible Pathway Gene Set Libraries for Enrichment Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("yuans-cellbio", email = "yuans@pitt.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Author: yuans-cellbio [aut, cre]
Maintainer: yuans-cellbio <yuans@pitt.edu>
Description: Build pathway gene set libraries from GO, MSigDB, KEGG, Reactome,
    PROGENy, and CollecTRI with a species-aware API and reproducible provenance.
    The package also provides helper functions for loading GMT libraries and
    running ORA or GSEA with consistent signed versus unsigned conventions.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: 
    R (>= 4.1)
Imports:
    AnnotationDbi,
    GO.db,
    Matrix
Suggests:
    clusterProfiler,
    decoupleR,
    dplyr,
    KEGGREST,
    msigdbr,
    OmnipathR,
    org.Hs.eg.db,
    org.Mm.eg.db,
    org.Rn.eg.db,
    progeny,
    reactome.db,
    testthat
Config/testthat/edition: 3
